{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce Licensing for Mobile Phones to Prevent Scams and Protect Consumers",
        "additional_details": "Counterfeit mobile phones are being sold as genuine on social media, online marketplaces, and second-hand websites. Once connected to the home internet, these devices can steal personal data and passwords without the buyer\u2019s knowledge, similar to a Trojan Horse virus that copies the user's keyboard input unbeknown to the buyer.  We think a licensing system would verify devices and link them to account holders, protecting consumers, reducing cybercrime, and enhancing mobile security in today's tech world.",
        "background": "Introduce a licensing system for all mobile phones in the UK, including contract and pay-as-you-go devices. Require phones to be verified and linked to an account holder, ensuring they are genuine, secure, and preventing counterfeit phones from being used to steal users\u2019 personal data.",
